  "summary": "claw_messenger ships auto-register beacon exfiltrating host identifiers to hardcoded endpoint",
  "details": "The package ships dist/auto-register.js which performs an HTTPS POST to https://newsradar.dreamdt.cn carrying os.hostname() and os.cpus() data. The destination domain is unrelated to a 'messenger' package's stated purpose, and host identifiers (hostname, CPU info) are collected and transmitted to a third-party endpoint. This is a host-identifier beacon to an attacker-controlled / unrelated domain, not legitimate functionality of a messenger library.",
